libdaemon
------------------------------------------
libdaemon is a lightweight C library that eases the writing of UNIX
daemons. It consists of the following parts:
  * A wrapper around fork() which does the correct daemonization
    procedure of a process
  * A wrapper around syslog() for simpler and compatible log output to
    Syslog or STDERR
  * An API for writing PID files
  * An API for serializing UNIX signals into a pipe for usage with
    select() or poll()
  * An API for running subprocesses with STDOUT and STDERR redirected
    to syslog.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.24-2

Build requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  autoconf2.5-2.61-1
  automake1.9-1.9.6-2
  binutils-20050817-1
  cygport-0.3.5-1
  gawk-3.1.5-4
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  libtool1.5-1.5.23a-2
  make-3.81-1
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://0pointer.de/lennart/projects/libdaemon/

Canonical download:
  http://0pointer.de/lennart/projects/libdaemon/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libdaemon-0.12-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libdaemon-0.12-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libdaemon-0.12-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libdaemon-0.12-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libdaemon-devel-0.12-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libdaemon0-0.12-X.tar.bz2

